panels.text:
## This page shows the list of indices we use in the Query Librarian.

## The list them here so you can both see the data, and also use sample queries.

## The list will grow, and evolve as this application evolves.

queries.queryString:
_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| sum(data_retrieved_bytes) as total_data_served
| int( total_data_served / 1G ) as total_gb_served
| fields total_gb_served

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query, retrieved_message_count, query_start_time, query_end_time
| sum(retrieved_message_count) as total_messages
| int(total_messages / 1000000) as total_messages

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query, query_start_time, query_end_time
| sum(_count) as total_messages

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count_distinct(user_name) as number_users

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query 
| where query contains ("_index=")
| replace (query, "  ", " ") as query
| replace (query, "  ", " ") as query
| replace (query, "  ", " ") as query
| parse regex field=query "_index=(?<my_item_name>\w+\s?)" multi
| where !( my_item_name contains("*") )
| where !( my_item_name contains("sumologic_") )
| where !( my_item_name contains("cloudtrail_") )
| count by my_item_name
| sort by _count

panels.text:
## Operators  Documentation Exaplanation

## On the left is a list of tthe known operators that we have. The query also shows you how to make a query using concat and tourl. The result? A targeted lookup for a well defined operator!

## Metavariables Documentaion Explanation

## On the right is a list of special variables, or metta variables that come into being as a result of using a query or ingesting data within Sumo Logic. Instead of using a precise URL, we put together a string to show how you can pass parameters into an existing URL. The result? A URL that allows you to search through our documentation.

queries.queryString:
_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by user_name

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where user_name matches "{{target_user}}"
| count by user_name
| compare with timeshift 1d 3
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query 
| where user_name matches "{{target_user}}"
| timeslice 15m 
| count by _timeslice 
| outlier _count window=5, threshold=1, consecutive=2, direction=+-

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| avg(execution_duration_ms) as average_duration
| average_duration / 1s as duration_sec
| fields duration_sec

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| execution_duration_ms / 1s as duration_in_seconds
| count as query_count by duration_in_seconds
| sort by duration_in_seconds

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where query contains("{{grep_target}}")
| count by query
| fields - _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query_type
| sort by _count

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| count by query
| replace(query, "\n", "|") as my_query
| replace(my_query, " ", "|") as my_query
| parse regex field=my_query "(?<verb>\w+)\|" multi nodrop
| where !( isBlank(verb) )
| where !( verb matches "_*" )
| where !( verb matches "time_range" )
| lookup documentation from path://"/Library/Users/wschmidt@sumologic.com/Sumo_Logic_Librarian/SumoLogic-Documentation" on operator=verb
| fields query, verb, documentation
| where !( isBlank(documentation ) )
| tourl(documentation, verb) as doclink
| count by verb, doclink
| sort by _count
| limit 10

_index=sumologic_search_usage_per_query
| where query contains("{{grep_target}}")
| limit {{results_limit}}
| urlencode(query) as query_urlencode
| toLong(queryStartTime()) as query_start
| toLong(queryEndTime()) as query_final
| concat("@", query_start, ",", query_final) as query_range
| tourl(concat("https://service.", "{{my_location}}", ".sumologic.com/ui/#/search/", query_range, "@", query_urlencode), "Run This Query!") as query_url
| count by query, query_url
| fields - _count
